Stimulation of three different microglial cells some hundreds of microns apart gave a Ca2 +  response in microglia at highest density closest to the site of stimulation. Our model quantitatively explains these observations as arising from the large amount of ATP released by the stimulated microglial cell diffusing to activate microglia within about 100 \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
